//]]&gt;
</script>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<div class="fb-post" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/apmmarketplace/posts/10152279953800148:0" data-width="466"><div class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/apmmarketplace/posts/10152279953800148:0">Post</a> by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/apmmarketplace">APM: Marketplace</a>.</div></div>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><br /><br /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>And on <a href="http://www.twitter.com/livemoney">Twitter</a>,<br /><br /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><p><a href="https://twitter.com/LiveMoney">@LiveMoney</a> Used to be very important when I had to go to an actual store and buy music, not so much any more.</p> — Daryl Paranada (@darylparanada) <a href="https://twitter.com/darylparanada/statuses/440575476017287169">March 3, 2014</a></blockquote>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<script async="" charset="utf-8" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" type="text/javascript">
</script>"},{"content":"<p><br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>And, for fun, we asked:<br /><br /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><p><a href="https://twitter.com/LiveMoney">@LiveMoney</a> 1.) first CD i bought was Ricky Martin. 2.) Last CD I bought was Perry Como. 3.) Goodness, that would be amazing.</p> — Zac Bissonnette (@ZacBissonnette) <a href="https://twitter.com/ZacBissonnette/statuses/440980511033274368">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<script async="" charset="utf-8" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" type="text/javascript">
</script>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p>A couple of our listeners agreed to talk with us about how their music buying habits have changed.</p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>John Cummings in Westlake Village, CA paid less than a dollar for his first big record store purchase.<br /><br /></p>"},{"content":"<p><iframe frameborder="no" scrolling="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/138476636&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_artwork=true"></iframe><br /><br /> Helena Okolicsanyi in Manassas, VA is big on supporting artists she loves by buying their CDs and attending live shows:<br /><br /><iframe frameborder="no" scrolling="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/138476636&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_artwork=true"></iframe><br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>And Mavis Gragg, a 38-year-old attorney in Washington, DC says she is determined to beef up her music collection again.  Here’s why:<br /><br /></p>"},{"content":"<p><iframe frameborder="no" scrolling="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/138480373&amp;color=ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_artwork=true"></iframe><br /><br /> Like Mavis, I don’t want to be the kind of person who doesn’t have my own music library. I want to have tangible access to the songs I love, and be able to hand them down to my children – even if they make fun of me for delighting in archaic formats like compact discs.<br /><br /> Which, if you haven’t listened to one in a while, sound amazing, by the way.<br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><em>What are your memories as a music consumer? Tell us about the first album you bought, or the last, and your relationship with owning music in the age of free streaming.  Leave a comment below or Tweet us <a href="http://twitter.com/livemoney">@LiveMoney.</a></em></p>","type":"text/html"}]
